        KEYWORDS="unicode editors"
           SHORT='Unicode text editor for X11'
cat << EOF
Yudit is a unicode text editor for the X Window System. She can do True
Type font rendering, printing, transliterated keyboard input and
handwriting recognition with no dependencies on on external engines.
Her conversion utilities can convert text between various encodings.
Keyboard input maps can also act like text converters. There is no need
for a pre-installed multi-lingual environment. Menus are translated
into many languages.
EOF
